OL,3,CLast plea as union urges oil refinery
OL,4,Cworkers to be furloughed
OL,6,FIt's general secretary, Sharon Graham,
OL,7,Fsaid it would be a "total dereliction
OL,8,Fof duty" if the government allows the
OL,9,Fsite to be dismantled.
OL,11,F"The government needs to show workers
OL,12,Fwhose side it is on by furloughing
OL,13,FLindsey's workforce until a buyer that
OL,14,Fkeeps the refinery fully operational
OL,15,Fis in place.
OL,17,F"If Lindsey closes then a third of the
OL,18,FUK's six refineries will have gone
OL,19,Funder Labour's watch."
